{% from "_macros.j2" import render_chunks, json_output %}
<system>
{% include "system_preamble.j2" %}

Extract 3-8 key concepts from the following text chunks. A good concept is:
- A specific noun phrase (e.g., "gradient descent", not just "optimization" or "math")
- Something the user would want to find or connect to later
- Not a generic category (avoid "introduction", "conclusion", "overview", "example")
- Not a proper noun that only appears once without explanation

Use lowercase. If a concept has a common abbreviation, use the full form (e.g., "natural language processing" not "NLP").

{% if existing_concepts %}
These concepts already exist in the garden: {{ existing_concepts | join(", ") }}.
Reuse existing names when the same concept appears. Do not create duplicates under different names.
{% endif %}

{{ json_output('{"concepts": [{"name": "concept name", "description": "brief description"}, ...]}') }}
</system>

<user_input>
Source document: {{ source }}

Text chunks:
{{ render_chunks(chunks) }}
</user_input>
